      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Here's a professional, well-structured conclusion report you can directly paste into your Jupyter notebook as a markdown cell:\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Final Report: Spam Message Detection using Machine Learning\n",
        "\n",
        "### Project Summary\n",
        "\n",
        "This project focused on building a **spam classification model** to distinguish between spam and ham (non-spam) SMS messages using supervised machine learning techniques. The pipeline involved:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Text preprocessing and cleaning\n",
        "- TF-IDF vectorization of messages\n",
        "- Model training and performance evaluation\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Models Evaluated\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Naive Bayes Classifier**\n",
        "2. **Logistic Regression (Baseline)**\n",
        "3. **XGBoost Classifier (Gradient Boosted Trees)**\n",
        "\n",
        "Each model was trained on TF-IDF features and evaluated using accuracy, precision, recall, and f1-score.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Final Results\n",
        "\n",
        "| Model              | Accuracy | Precision (Spam) | Recall (Spam) | F1-Score (Spam) |\n",
        "|-------------------|----------|------------------|---------------|-----------------|\n",
        "| Naive Bayes       | 97.8%    | 0.99             | 0.84          | 0.91            |\n",
        "| XGBoost           | 97.6%    | 0.94             | 0.88          | 0.91            |\n",
        "| Final Optimized   | 97.0%    | 1.00             | 0.78          | 0.88            |\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Observations\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Naive Bayes performed best overall**, with high precision and recall balance for spam detection.\n",
        "- **XGBoost showed comparable results**, capturing deeper patterns at the cost of slightly lower recall.\n",
        "- The **final optimized model** reached perfect precision but missed more spam messages, affecting recall.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Conclusion\n",
        "\n",
        "The Naive Bayes classifier remains an excellent choice for spam classification when paired with TF-IDF features. Despite experimenting with more complex models like XGBoost, the simplicity and effectiveness of Naive Bayes made it the top performer.\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "dBnXVMVMc7oT"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# **Further improvements**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "f7sdE95CdAZ2"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Install dependencies (uncomment if needed)\n",
        "# !pip install transformers datasets openpyxl\n",
        "\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, precision_recall_fscore_support\n",
        "from transformers import BertTokenizerFast, BertForSequenceClassification, Trainer, TrainingArguments\n",
        "from datasets import Dataset\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Load your dataset\n",
        "df = pd.read_excel(\"train.xlsx\")\n",
        "df = df[['sms', 'label']].dropna()\n",
        "df.columns = ['text', 'label']\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Clean the text column\n",
        "df['text'] = df['text'].astype(str).str.lower()\n",
        "df['text'] = df['text'].str.replace(r'\\W+', ' ', regex=True).str.replace(r'\\s+', ' ', regex=True).str.strip()\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Check dataset status\n",
        "print(\" Sample count:\", len(df))\n",
        "print(df['label'].value_counts())\n",
        "if df.empty:\n",
        "    raise ValueError(\" The DataFrame is empty after preprocessing.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. Train-test split\n",
        "train_df, test_df = train_test_split(df, test_size=0.2, stratify=df['label'], random_state=42)\n",
        "train_ds = Dataset.from_pandas(train_df.reset_index(drop=True))\n",
        "test_ds = Dataset.from_pandas(test_df.reset_index(drop=True))\n",
        "\n",
        "# 5. Tokenization using BERT\n",
        "tokenizer = BertTokenizerFast.from_pretrained(\"bert-base-uncased\")\n",
        "def tokenize_function(examples):\n",
        "    return tokenizer(examples['text'], padding=\"max_length\", truncation=True, max_length=128)\n",
        "train_ds = train_ds.map(tokenize_function, batched=True)\n",
        "test_ds = test_ds.map(tokenize_function, batched=True)\n",
        "train_ds.set_format(type='torch', columns=['input_ids', 'attention_mask', 'label'])\n",
        "test_ds.set_format(type='torch', columns=['input_ids', 'attention_mask', 'label'])\n",
        "\n",
        "# 6. Load pre-trained BERT model\n",
        "model = BertForSequenceClassification.from_pretrained(\"bert-base-uncased\", num_labels=2)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 7. Define metrics for evaluation\n",
        "def compute_metrics(pred):\n",
        "    labels = pred.label_ids\n",
        "    preds = pred.predictions.argmax(-1)\n",
        "    precision, recall, f1, _ = precision_recall_fscore_support(labels, preds, average='binary')\n",
        "    acc = accuracy_score(labels, preds)\n",
        "    return {\"accuracy\": acc, \"precision\": precision, \"recall\": recall, \"f1\": f1}\n",
        "\n",
        "# 8. Training arguments\n",
        "training_args = TrainingArguments(\n",
        "    output_dir=\"./bert-results\",\n",
        "    do_train=True,\n",
        "    do_eval=True,\n",
        "    per_device_train_batch_size=16,\n",
        "    per_device_eval_batch_size=64,\n",
        "    learning_rate=2e-5,\n",
        "    num_train_epochs=3,\n",
        "    logging_dir=\"./logs\",\n",
        "    logging_steps=10,\n",
        "    save_total_limit=1\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 9. Trainer setup\n",
        "trainer = Trainer(\n",
        "    model=model,\n",
        "    args=training_args,\n",
        "    train_dataset=train_ds,\n",
        "    eval_dataset=test_ds,\n",
        "    tokenizer=tokenizer,\n",
        "    compute_metrics=compute_metrics\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 10. Train and evaluate\n",
        "trainer.train()\n",
        "results = trainer.evaluate()\n",
        "print(\"\\n Final Evaluation Results:\")\n",
        "print(results)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
